# Architecture Rules

## Folder Structure (Enforced)

```
src/
  app/               ← Route entry only. No business logic.
  features/
    scenario-engine/ ← Shared scenario domain + application layer
    coffee/
    laundry/
    cooking/
  shared/            ← Cross-feature reusable code
  server/            ← Server-side only (services, validators, AI adapter)
```

## Layer Responsibilities

| Layer | Allowed | Forbidden |
|-------|---------|-----------|
| `app/` | Route, layout, page composition | Business logic, direct DB/API calls |
| `features/*/domain/` | Types, constants, pure domain functions | UI imports, server imports |
| `features/*/application/` | Plan builders, command handlers, pure logic | UI state, React hooks |
| `features/*/ui/` | React components, hooks | Direct domain mutation, server calls |
| `server/` | Services, validators, AI adapter | React, client state |
| `shared/` | Generic components, utils, hooks | Feature-specific logic |

## Module Boundary Rules

- `features/coffee` must NOT import from `features/laundry` or `features/cooking`
- `features/*/domain` must NOT import from `features/*/ui`
- `server/` must NOT import from `features/*/ui`
- `app/` must NOT contain business logic — delegate to features or server
- `shared/` must NOT import from `features/`

## Scenario Engine Interface (Required)

Every scenario MUST implement `BaseScenario<TState, TResources>`:

```typescript
interface BaseScenario<TState, TResources> {
  id: string;
  scenarioType: ScenarioType;
  title: string;
  resources: TResources;
  currentState: TState;
  plan: Step[];
  warnings: Warning[];
  substitutions: Substitution[];
}
```

## Server / Client Boundary

- Default to React Server Components
- Add `'use client'` only when interactivity or browser APIs are needed
- 3D components (React Three Fiber) MUST use `'use client'` + `dynamic({ ssr: false })`
- Never import server-only modules (`server/`, `fs`, `crypto`) in client components

## AI Adapter Pattern

```
UI → Zustand Action → Server Action / API Route → AIAdapter → LLM Provider
                                                ↘ Zod Validate ↙
                                                  Typed Command
                                                       ↓
                                              Fallback if invalid
```

- AI calls are isolated in `src/server/services/aiAdapter.ts`
- All AI output is validated with Zod before use in application logic
- Deterministic fallback must always exist

## Named Exports Only

```typescript
// ✅ Good
export function buildCoffeePlan(...) {}
export type { CoffeeState };

// ❌ Bad
export default function buildCoffeePlan(...) {}
```

## One Responsibility Per File

- One file = one primary concern
- Colocate types with their usage if they are not shared
- Move to `shared/types/` only if used across 2+ features
